                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Paris"
                    },
                    "body": "There is actually a discussion to relax the utf8 requirement in IPC metadata values (see the message recently posted by [~jorisvandenbossche]\u00a0 \"Re: [DISCUSS] Binary Values in Key value pairs WAS: Re: [INFO_REQUEST][FLIGHT] - Dynamic schema changes in ArrowFlight streams\").\r\n\r\nIn short: yes, Arrow C++ and PyArrow can put arbitrary binary data in metadata values.\r\n\r\nAlso cc [~lidavidm] \u00a0[~emkornfield]\u00a0",
