                        },
                        "displayName": "Joris Van den Bossche",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Brussels"
                    },
                    "body": "(Side note: this might be just for quick testing, but if you actually want to use the extension type on the rust side as well, you should probably define the extension type in Python as a subclass of {{pyarrow.ExtensionType}}, and not {{pyarrow.PyExtensionType}}, since the latter uses a pickle dump of the class as the serialized metadata, which you won't be able to use in Rust, I suppose)",
